# Cloudflare Pages _redirects — one rule per line.
# Syntax: <source> <destination> <status>
#
# Real fix for client-side routing lives in App.tsx (BrowserRouter).
# This file ensures Cloudflare Pages serves index.html for any path
# the SPA owns, so a direct visit to /about loads the React app and
# react-router renders the correct view.
#
# Examples:
#   /old-path           /new-path            301
#   /docs/*             /documentation/:splat 301
#
# Add real redirect rules above this line as the site evolves.

# No SPA wildcard fallback rule. Each route is prerendered to its own
# dist/<route>/index.html (see scripts/prerender.mjs) and served as a real
# 200 file. Unknown routes hit dist/404.html, which Cloudflare Pages serves
# automatically — the SPA shell loads inside that 404 response, React Router
# renders <NotFound /> for the actual URL, and crawlers see a proper 404
# status (instead of the soft-404 a 200-rewrite would produce).
#
# Pages Functions in /functions match before any rules here, so /api/*
# endpoints continue to hit the function as before.
